Considering rockfall frequency, volume and permafrost involvement, we can clearly see the impact of the global warming. Besides overall huge variability between single years, in the last decades both the volume and number of rockfalls have significantly increased. The number of rockfalls, caused by permafrost degradation, rised as well, which shows the effect of climate change.

Uncertainties are largely due to the long history of observations. While in the pre Satellite area before 1972, with the merge of Landsat, especcially smaller rockfalls in remote areas, where not observed or reported (Heipke 2017). 


